      "side": 1,
      "message": "If an animation is fairly short, then the sample might not last as long as sampleDuration. I think we need to keep looping in that case until we have exceeded a duration of sampleDuration.\n\nHow would you feel about replacing the \"draw_skp_and_flush/gpySync.sync\" lines with a virtual method? Then it would look like:\n\n\nint StaticSkp::drawAndFlushAndSync(surface, GpuSync\u0026 gpuSync) {\n    draw_skp_and_flush(...);\n    gpuSync.syncToPreviousFrame();\n    return 1;\n}\n\nAnimatedSkp::drawAndFlushAndSync(surface, GpuSync\u0026 sync) {\n    for (;;) {\n        draw_skp_and_flush(...);\n        gpuSync.syncToPreviousFrame();\n    }\n    return mskp-\u003ecount();\n}\n\n\n... run_benchmark() {\n...\n            do {\n                sample.fFrames +\u003d skpThingy-\u003edrawAndFlushAndSync(surface, gpuSync);\n                now \u003d clock::now();\n                sample.fDuration \u003d now - sampleStart;\n            } while (sample.fDuration \u003c sampleDuration);",
